the problems? I believe it is to fix the problems without denying anyone GA who currently qualifies. &#10;When there is a problem with emergency service funding (ambulance, police, fire, etc), is the answer to deny people from receiving emergency services? Or is it to fix the problems? I believe it is to fix the problems without denying anyone emergency services who currently qualifies. &#10;When there is a problem with transportation funding -- busses, trains, subways, etc -- is the answer to deny people the use of public transportation? Or is it to fix the problems? I believe it is to continue operating public transportation as much as possible while fixing the funding problems. &#10;So if there is a problem with school service funding, such that supporting homeschoolers takes money away from public school students, my answer is not to stop supporting homeschoolers. It's to fix the funding problems, so that all students are supported, regardless of where the bulk of their academic education takes place. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1308" language="en" documentId="670" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="KRAMV" date="09/06/2013" docType="forumpost" origUrl="http://community.babycenter.com/post/a44369503/home_schooling_debate_this_hypothetical?cpg=39" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="670" notes="" title="Home schooling: Debate this hypothetical"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="123"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="124" end="162"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="163" end="400"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="401" end="685"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="55" sofa="1" begin="686" end="981"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="59" sofa="1" begin="982" end="1308"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51 55 59"/></xmi:XMI>